{code:java}
Error : Placeholder mismatch
English : [{0}] {1} invited you to edit "{2}"
Translated: Użytkownik [{0}] {0} zaprasza Cię do redakcji „{2}"{code}

h3. Issue Summary

The People Directory screen has a translatable string that could get improved.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Change your confluence language to Brazilian Portuguese
 # In the top bar select in {{More > Usuários}}
 # In the text box type {{*inexistente*}} (or any other user name you are sure it does not exists in your Confluence instance) and click {{Pesquisar}}

h3. Expected Results

You should get an empty list with a message saying that no users were found (in Portuguese) that is consistent with the screen.
h3. Actual Results

The returned message {{"Não foram encontrados utilizadores."}} does not make sense in Portuguese. {{Users}} are commonly translated to {{usuários}}, so a better option would be {{"Nenhum usuário encontrado."}}

 

On that screen, all the texts were mentioning {{users}} as {{pessoas}}, what is fine, so for the sake of consistency on that screen, I'd suggest to translate it to {{"Nenhuma pessoa encontrada."}}

 
h3. Workaround

Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available
